; 翌朝・酒場の受付
; ブルーに強引に仕事を押しつけられる
@bg f=0015
@mu f=town
[texton]
And the next day.[k]
[マックス f=03]「All right! I got a perfect job today!」[k]
[テオ f=02]「It was worth it to get in line early in the morning. If we do this every day, we're sure to make a lot of money.」[k]
Max and I packed the bar early in the morning, determined to get a job ourselves, no matter what it took.[k]
If we did the work that Blue was contracted to do, that didn't earn us nearly as much as we could earn ourselves.[k]
We realized that we had to take action ourselves if we wanted to make money.[k]
[マックス f=01]「Well, the deadline is this evening, so we can't afford to take things too easy. Let's go out as soon as possible!」[k]
@st
